Summary Quantitative professional specializing in the financial risk management arena. Experience with bringing a financial risk management SaaS solution to market from the design stage to final implementation. Extensive knowledge of database-driven reporting, methods in financial modeling and stress testing/simulation techniques of fixed income, equity, derivatives, credit, FX and structured products. Entrepreneurial and motivated, a versatile programmer with client-facing experience. Summary Quantitative professional specializing in the financial risk management arena. Experience with bringing a financial risk management SaaS solution to market from the design stage to final implementation. Extensive knowledge of database-driven reporting, methods in financial modeling and stress testing/simulation techniques of fixed income, equity, derivatives, credit, FX and structured products. Entrepreneurial and motivated, a versatile programmer with client-facing experience. Quantitative professional specializing in the financial risk management arena. Experience with bringing a financial risk management SaaS solution to market from the design stage to final implementation. Extensive knowledge of database-driven reporting, methods in financial modeling and stress testing/simulation techniques of fixed income, equity, derivatives, credit, FX and structured products. Entrepreneurial and motivated, a versatile programmer with client-facing experience. Quantitative professional specializing in the financial risk management arena. Experience with bringing a financial risk management SaaS solution to market from the design stage to final implementation. Extensive knowledge of database-driven reporting, methods in financial modeling and stress testing/simulation techniques of fixed income, equity, derivatives, credit, FX and structured products. Entrepreneurial and motivated, a versatile programmer with client-facing experience. Experience Quantitative Strategist Quantifi, Inc. October 2013  –  September 2014  (1 year) Greater New York City Area Within the Client Services team, I was responsible for several client accounts including hedge funds, global banks and corporates. I oversaw client implementations including planning and scheduling, project scoping, and subsequent integration with Quantifi’s software. As one of the quantitative experts within the team, I often worked with clients to understand their unique needs and assisted development in enhancing our software to support new functionality. I regularly engaged in presales, client demos, and constructed proof-of-concepts demonstrating Quantifi’s award-winning capabilities when entering into new client relationships. 

- Performed full client risk implementations including Market Risk, Counterparty Risk and CVA. 
- Improved integration with market data providers including Markit, Bloomberg, Reuters, and Intex. 
- Extensive experience with CLO modelling. 
- Assisted in implementation of cutting-edge financial models. Financial Engineer IBM January 2012  –  September 2013  (1 year 9 months) Waltham, MA As a member of the product management team within IBM Risk Analytics, I was responsible for the architecture, construction, and implementation of cutting-edge risk management solutions. I was the lead Financial Engineer of IBM Algo Risk Reports on Cloud, an automated risk management reporting SaaS application used by hedge funds to comply with international regulatory standards and gain insights into their risk exposures. I regularly contributed to multiple projects and client needs simultaneously across production and development environments. Other projects included a workflow management tool used by European insurance companies, a Solvency II asset-management service, and an automated replicating portfolio solution.  

-Modeled financial instruments spanning multiple asset classes including: Equity Multi-Factor Models, Willow-Tree lattice-based fixed income models, Monte Carlo asset-backed prepayment models, Credit and Credit Derivative models, and exotic derivative models;  
-Responsible for construction of topical and regulatory scenario sets on market risk factors; 
-Implemented and maintained database models using database software, including Oracle; 
-Programmed scripts to integrate components into an automated process; 
-Built compliance reports for UCITS IV and Dodd-Frank Form PF using Business Objects and IBM Cognos BI software infrastructure; 
-Designed and implemented a tool to extract market data from third-party providers to use as input parameters to financial models; 
-Frequently contributed proposals and specifications to add new features and functionality to new and existing software; 
-Applied an in-house optimization framework for creation of replicating portfolios of assets that map to insurance liabilities. 

